At least eight persons were confirmed to have lost their lives in a road accident that occurred on Thursday in Taraba State. It was gathered that the accident which occurred along Iware / Wukari highway involved an 18-seater Toyota bus. The State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Usman Abdullahi who confirmed the incident said the accident was caused by a tyre bust. NSSF Auctions WeNaija Photography Competitionâ€™s Top Images Boko Haram Terrorists Strike On Borno, Abduct Policemen According to him, the tyre bust, and the driver of the vehicle lost control and it somersaulted several times. It was further leant that seven of the passengers died on the spot, while the other one gave up the ghost while being rushed to hospital for medication. One out of the nine passengers was also confirmed to have sustained various degrees of injuries and is presently undergoing treatment at the emergency ward of the Federal Medical Centre, Jalingo. The vehicle was said to have left Jalingo, the State capital heading to Enugu State when the ill-fated accident occurred.